  <font size=4 color="000080"><a name="top"><b>Administrator Help - Users Section</b></font><br>
  <hr size=1 noshade>
  The <b>Users</b> section allows you to administer the users on your site.  You can
  add new users directly from this page, or edit existing ones.  You can also
  disable (inactivate) or delete any user account you wish.
  <br><br>
  <b>Explanation of page elements</b>

  <br><br>
  <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3>
   <tr>
    <td valign="top"><img src="./user8.jpg" alt="Screenshot" width=500 height=900></td>
    <td valign="top">
     <font size=2>      
      <font size=3 color="008000"><b>Edit and Delete Feedback Section:</b></font><br><br>
      <b>Edit and delete feedback:</b><br>This gives you the control of the feedback left for user's.<br><br>
      <font size=3 color="008000"><b>User Info Section:</b></font><br><br>
      <b>Name:</b><br>The full name of the user.<br><br>
      <b>Nickname:</b><br>The user's nickname.  This defaults to their user ID.<br><br>
      <b>Password:</b><br>The user's password they chose to use.<br><br>
      <b>Keyword:</b><br>A keyword the user can use to recover their password should they forget it.<br><br>
      <b>Company:</b><br>The user's company (if any).<br><br>
      <b>E-mail address:</b><br>The user's email address.<br><br>
      <b>Email me when:</b><br>Here is where the user can control the emails he or she receives from you. They choose these options when they register but you can update it for them from here.<br><br>
      <b>Phone 1, Phone 2, Fax:</b><br>The user's primary, secondary, and fax numbers, respectively.<br><br>
      <b>Balance and Credit:</b><br>Balance shows the user's outstanding balance. Credit this amount will appear if the user has overpaid and leaves them with a credit or you issue a refund.<br><br>
      <b>Credit Card Holder:</b><br>Name of individual or corporation as it appears on card.<br><br>
      <b>Credit Card Number:</b><br>16 digit number as it appears on card.<br><br>
      <b>Credit Card Expiration:</b><br>Expiration date as it appears on card.<br><br>
      <b>Address, city, state, postal code, country:</b><br>The user's location information.<br><br>
      <b>Shipping Information:</b><br>Checking this box means the user's mailing and shipping address are the same.<br><br>
      <b>Shipping Address, city, state, postal code, country:</b><br>The user's shipping location information.<br><br>
      </table> 
      <font size=3 color="008000"><b>Optional Information Section:</b></font><br><br>
      <b>Membership:</b><br>This option can be used by the member to pay a flat rate instead of by each auction listing.<br><br>
      <b>Referred by:</b><br>The email address of who referred them to the site.<br><br>
      <b>Language:</b><br>The language they prefer to communicate in.<br><br>
      <b>Heard from:</b><br>Relation of the person who told them about the site.<br><br>
      <b>Site use:</b><br>What they primarily use the site for.<br>
     </font>
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td colspan=2>
     <font size=2>
      <br>
      <b>Interested in:</b><br>What the user is primarily interested in on the site.<br><br>      
      <b>Education level &amp; income:</b><br>What level of education the user has completed and what their annual household income is.<br><br>      
      <b>Promotion code:</b><br>If the user received a promotional code, then it is recorded here.<br><br>      
      <b>Age range &amp; gender:</b><br>The user's age range and gender.<br><br>      
      

      
      <b>Would like to participate in surveys:</b><br>If this box is checked, the user will be asked to participate in online surveys, when this features is available and configured properly.<br><br>      
      <b>Is on the mailing list:</b><br>If this box is checked, the user has given permission to be sent periodic e-mails announcing items and new features.<br><br>
      <b>User is active:</b><br>If this box is checked, the user's account is active and they can log in.  If this box is not checked, the user cannot log in and only the administrator can re-enable them.<br><br>
      <b>User Confirmation:</b><br>If this box is checked, the user's account has been confirmed by clicking the link in their registration email and they can log in.  If this box is not checked, the user cannot log in.<br><br>
     <font color="red"><font size=3> <b>Full Control:</font size=3></font color="red"></b><br>If this box is checked, This will allow seller to delete bids as well as cancel or delete their auctions. This option really should not be given to all members.<br><br>
      
      <hr size=1 noshade><font size=3 color="008000"><b>User List Section:</b></font><br><br>
      The user list section of the user administrator shows a list of the current users
      registered on your auction site.  Inactive users have [brackets] around their nickname
      (or user ID if they haven't specified a nickname yet).<br><br>
      The buttons marked "Retrieve", "Disable", and "Delete" are used to get more info
      on a particular user, disable, or delete their account, respectively.<br><br>
      The search text box and button above the user list is used to search for a particular
      user, or to narrow down the number of users displayed in the list box.  You
      can search for user ID, name, and nickname by entering the information you
      wish to find in the search box and clicking the "Search" button.
      <br><br>

     </font>

    </td>
   </tr>
  </table> 
  <br>   
  <b>Once you have entered all the information or are done editing, click the
  <font color="#ff0000">"Add User"</font> button to save the data.  Otherwise click the <font color="#ff0000">"Clear Form"</font> button to
  clear the form and start over.</b><br>
